1
00:00:00,404 --> 00:00:02,482
 <I>Previously On "Ugly Betty"...</I>
(Betty) You Have
A Secret Husband?

2
00:00:02,482 --> 00:00:04,998
Booze And Pills Weren't Enough?
I'm Sick.

3
00:00:05,149 --> 00:00:07,469
If I Can't Marry
Into The Meade Family,

4
00:00:08,284 --> 00:00:11,600
I Will Give Birth To An Heir.

5
00:00:11,650 --> 00:00:13,683
We Need To Find A Surrogate
We Can Control,

6
00:00:13,683 --> 00:00:17,601
Someone Who's Desperate
For Money.
I'm The Editor-In-Chief
Of "Mode,"

7
00:00:17,601 --> 00:00:20,727
And This Office
Is Now A Nursery.
But I'm Your Father,

8
00:00:20,727 --> 00:00:23,658
You Are My Son,
And We're In This Together.

9
00:00:23,658 --> 00:00:25,859
You're Telling Me
That You're Married?
I Just Wanted You To Know

10
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:28,203
Because I Feel
Like I'm Falling For You.

11
00:00:28,551 --> 00:00:31,145
Betty, Hey!
Welcome To Our New Home.

12
00:00:31,145 --> 00:00:33,625
I Really Want To Take On
More Responsibility.

13
00:00:33,658 --> 00:00:37,488
I Just... I Thought That
That Was Gonna Be At "Mode."

14
00:00:50,059 --> 00:00:51,992
Daniel...
(Man Speaking Indistinctly)

15
00:00:52,025 --> 00:00:53,925
When I Said
That "Player" Magazine

16
00:00:53,959 --> 00:00:55,901
Should Show Women
In A More Professional Light,

17
00:00:55,901 --> 00:00:58,069
This Isn't Exactly
What I Had In Mind.

18
00:00:58,069 --> 00:01:01,885
Betty, That's Your Concept--
America's Hottest Lawyers.

19
00:01:01,885 --> 00:01:05,418
Um, I Pihed America's
Top Female Attorneys.

20
00:01:05,418 --> 00:01:07,341
Look, I Know This Is
"Player" Magazine,

21
00:01:07,374 --> 00:01:10,918
But Does <I>Every</I> Spread Have To Be
Women In Skimpy Bras?

22
00:01:10,918 --> 00:01:13,898
You Know What? You're Right.
I Hadn't Thought Of That.

23
00:01:13,898 --> 00:01:16,241
Let's Lose Those Bras,
Please.
(Man) Lose 'Em.

24
00:01:16,274 --> 00:01:18,207
No, That's Not What I Meant!

25
00:01:23,302 --> 00:01:25,497
That's Not What I Meant.

26
00:01:26,314 --> 00:01:28,353
What Are You Working On?

27
00:01:29,134 --> 00:01:31,249
Nothing. Just Doodling,
You Know.

28
00:01:31,426 --> 00:01:32,744
Is That "Mode"?

29
00:01:32,744 --> 00:01:34,172
No, It's Just, Uh,

30
00:01:34,209 --> 00:01:36,649
It's Just The Mock-Up
For Wilhelmina's First Issue,

31
00:01:36,649 --> 00:01:39,853
You Know.
I Knew It, Daniel. A Part Of You
Wants To Be Back At "Mode."

32
00:01:39,853 --> 00:01:42,680
No, Look. I Just Want To See
What Wilhelmina's Up To.

33
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,352
You Know Exactly
What She's Up To--

34
00:01:44,352 --> 00:01:47,305
Firing, Scheming,
Looking For A Puppy To Kick.

35
00:01:47,305 --> 00:01:49,738
Well, Then I'm Happy
To Be Away From It.

36
00:01:50,272 --> 00:01:52,290
See? Happy.

37
00:01:56,872 --> 00:01:59,005
It's Daniel's Copy
Of The Mock-Up.

38
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:01,846
Oh, Crap. I Forgot
We Still Send It To Him.

39
00:02:01,846 --> 00:02:04,972
I'll Make Sure
We Take Him Off The List.
Uh, No.
That's Not Why I Here.

40
00:02:05,005 --> 00:02:07,400
You See, Alexis, There Are
A Lot Of Notes In Here,

41
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:10,559
And They're Good.
I'm Sure He Has
A Lot Of Notes.

42
00:02:10,559 --> 00:02:13,151
It's Wilhelmina's First Issue,
And He Hates Wilhelmina.

43
00:02:13,151 --> 00:02:15,084
No, See,
These Aren't The Notes

44
00:02:15,084 --> 00:02:17,047
Of Somebody Who Wants
To Get To Wilhelmina.

45
00:02:17,382 --> 00:02:19,349
"Cover Is Too Obscure.
Will It Sell?

46
00:02:19,382 --> 00:02:22,609
Pull Up Key Ads. Where Is
'"Mode" Girl On Madison'?"

47
00:02:22,737 --> 00:02:25,386
Alexis, He Cares
About This Magazine.

48
00:02:25,386 --> 00:02:26,409
He Misses "Mode."

49
00:02:26,409 --> 00:02:29,315
I Mean, He Won't Admit It,
But He Belongs Here.

50
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:32,563
I Appreciate Your Loyalty
To Your Boss, Betty,

51
00:02:32,563 --> 00:02:35,519
But Daniel Doesn't Work
At "Mode" Anymore.

52
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,115
Okay.

53
00:02:38,585 --> 00:02:41,218
Well, Thanks For Your Time.

54
00:02:50,185 --> 00:02:51,585
What's Wrong?

55
00:02:51,619 --> 00:02:54,952
Nothing. What's More Romantic
Than Lunch On Foot

56
00:02:54,986 --> 00:02:57,130
With A View
Of Rikers Island?

57
00:02:58,318 --> 00:03:00,946
(Mouth Full) Okay.

58
00:03:01,752 --> 00:03:03,685
You Know,

59
00:03:03,719 --> 00:03:07,066
You Deserve Better
Than Week-Old Lamb.

60
00:03:07,785 --> 00:03:09,446
How About...

61
00:03:10,318 --> 00:03:11,819
A Real Date?

62
00:03:12,495 --> 00:03:13,619
(Gasps) Really?

63
00:03:13,652 --> 00:03:17,187
Yeah, Jill Got Called
For A Layover Flight
Leaving Wednesday Morning.

64
00:03:17,187 --> 00:03:19,028
I'm Thinking
Maybe Wednesday Night,

65
00:03:19,028 --> 00:03:21,678
 <I>We</I> Could Do Something Special.

66
00:03:25,685 --> 00:03:28,218
Hey. What--What Happened
To The Smile?

67
00:03:28,428 --> 00:03:29,552
No, Nothing.

68
00:03:29,585 --> 00:03:32,552
I Just Try To Forget
That You Have A Wife,

69
00:03:32,585 --> 00:03:35,619
But... You Have A Wife.

70
00:03:35,652 --> 00:03:37,619
And I Told You
How Things Stand.

71
00:03:37,652 --> 00:03:40,519
Coach, Everything
That You Said To Me

72
00:03:40,552 --> 00:03:44,151
About--About Us Having
A Future Together--

73
00:03:44,185 --> 00:03:46,452
Just Be Honest With Me,

74
00:03:46,485 --> 00:03:48,301
Is That For Real?

75
00:03:48,979 --> 00:03:50,418
I Promise.

76
00:03:50,452 --> 00:03:52,585
You're Not The Other Woman.

77
00:03:52,619 --> 00:03:54,552
You're The Only Woman.

78
00:03:56,318 --> 00:03:58,639
But If You Take This Shot
And Put It Right Here,

79
00:03:58,639 --> 00:04:02,134
It Draws Your Eye
Right To The Ad.
Alexis, We Go To Print Tonight.

80
00:04:02,135 --> 00:04:04,118
My Launch Party's
In Two Days.

81
00:04:04,151 --> 00:04:06,652
There's Time.
And What About This Cover?

82
00:04:06,685 --> 00:04:09,085
Angelina Jolie
In A Block Of Ice?

83
00:04:09,118 --> 00:04:12,318
I Mean, Do You Have A Shot
That's A Little Le Arty?

84
00:04:12,352 --> 00:04:14,621
Or At Least One
Where You Can See Who It Is?

85
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:18,552
Wait A Minute.
Those Aren't Your Notes. Ugh.

86
00:04:18,585 --> 00:04:23,252
Ah, The Rounded O's
Of A Stunted Adolescent,

87
00:04:23,285 --> 00:04:26,819
The Stiff T's Of Someone
Who's Clearly Overcompensating.

88
00:04:26,852 --> 00:04:28,886
This Is Daniel's Handwriting.

89
00:04:28,919 --> 00:04:33,151
J'accuse.
Yes, These Are Daniel's Notes,
And I Happen To Agree With Them.

90
00:04:33,185 --> 00:04:37,519
Why Is He Even Giving You Notes?
He Isn't. Betty Found Them
And Brought Them To Me.

91
00:04:37,552 --> 00:04:39,886
Now Why Don't You Put
Your Ego Aside For A Second

92
00:04:39,919 --> 00:04:42,619
And Just Admit
That Your Issue Needs Help?

93
00:04:42,652 --> 00:04:44,585
I Mean, Where's Our "'Mode' Girl
On Madison" Feature?

94
00:04:44,619 --> 00:04:47,085
Who Cares What The Average Woman
Wears On The Street?

95
00:04:47,118 --> 00:04:48,671
We Shouldn't
Be Taking Their Pictures.

96
00:04:48,671 --> 00:04:51,847
We Should Be Throwing Rocks
At Them.
I Think Our Readers Like It.

97
00:04:51,847 --> 00:04:53,837
Our Readers Like
What I Tell Them To Like.

98
00:04:53,837 --> 00:04:56,336
Look, We Agreed That "Mode"
Needed A Kick In The Ass.

99
00:04:56,336 --> 00:05:00,024
I'm Giving It
A Kick In The Ass.
I Never Tire
Of You Saying That.

100
00:05:00,773 --> 00:05:02,761
Just Take A Look
At Daniel's Notes.

101
00:05:03,365 --> 00:05:04,712
Of Course.

102
00:05:05,677 --> 00:05:07,004
Well, She--

103
00:05:07,982 --> 00:05:10,373
I See Someone's
Gonna Be A Problem.
Daniel?

104
00:05:10,373 --> 00:05:12,817
(Scoffs) Daniel Is
An Overripe Cantaloupe

105
00:05:12,817 --> 00:05:14,172
Tumbling Toward Irrelevance.

106
00:05:14,172 --> 00:05:16,021
I'm Talking About Betty.

107
00:05:16,292 --> 00:05:19,125
She's Trying To Get Daniel Back
In Here. <I>She's</I> The Problem.

108
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:23,394
Okay, Lunch.

109
00:05:27,306 --> 00:05:29,014
No Burrito For You.

110
00:05:29,014 --> 00:05:31,209
Marc, Why Did You Do That?

111
00:05:31,209 --> 00:05:33,408
You Have A Lunch Date.
With You?

112
00:05:33,408 --> 00:05:35,309
No. With Wilhelmina.

113
00:05:37,188 --> 00:05:38,642
(Woman) Mademoiselle.

114
00:05:38,676 --> 00:05:41,242
Look At Us--
Two Women Of Color

115
00:05:41,275 --> 00:05:44,509
Out For A Fancy Lunch
On The Town. (Chuckles)

116
00:05:44,942 --> 00:05:48,075
Isn't This Fun, Girlfriend?

117
00:05:48,228 --> 00:05:50,542
(Chuckles) I Guess.

118
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:54,041
And That Blouse Is Heaven.

119
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:56,044
Where Did You Get It?
I Love It.

120
00:05:56,044 --> 00:05:57,509
Okay. No, You Don't.

121
00:05:57,542 --> 00:05:59,008
No, I Don't.

122
00:05:59,042 --> 00:06:01,743
It's Hideous,
Like Driving Through Ohio.

123
00:06:01,776 --> 00:06:05,309
Look, Let's Cut To The Chase,
Betty. I Need You.

124
00:06:05,342 --> 00:06:06,609
What?

125
00:06:06,642 --> 00:06:08,109
You Kept Daniel's Files.

126
00:06:08,142 --> 00:06:10,542
Marc Can't Make
Heads Or Tails Of Them.

127
00:06:11,322 --> 00:06:13,918
Um, Okay. Yeah. Fine.

128
00:06:13,918 --> 00:06:17,054
I'll Ask Daniel
For A Little Bit Of Time
To Come And Work On Them.

129
00:06:17,054 --> 00:06:21,337
Or You Could Recognize
A Career Opportunity
When You See One.

130
00:06:22,022 --> 00:06:26,220
Betty, You Were The Assistant
To The Editor-In-Chief
At "Mode" Before.

131
00:06:26,422 --> 00:06:29,642
I Think It's Time You Return
To Where You Belong.

132
00:06:29,676 --> 00:06:32,142
Are You Offering Me A Job?

133
00:06:32,175 --> 00:06:35,382
At "Mode," Working For Me.

134
00:06:36,975 --> 00:06:40,072
Look, Wilhelmina,
I'm Not Leaving Daniel,

135
00:06:40,072 --> 00:06:43,452
And... To Be Frank...

136
00:06:43,743 --> 00:06:45,898
I Don't Really Trust You.

137
00:06:46,425 --> 00:06:49,409
Loyalty <I>And</I> Suspicion--

138
00:06:49,879 --> 00:06:51,811
Two Very Admirable Qualities.

139
00:06:52,975 --> 00:06:55,489
Betty, You Belong At "Mode,"

140
00:06:55,489 --> 00:06:57,719
And I Think Daniel
Would Understand.

141
00:06:57,719 --> 00:07:00,860
Well, I Think Daniel Will Say
That You Want To Hire Me

142
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:03,242
To Ask Me To Do
Very Bad, Bad Things.

143
00:07:03,275 --> 00:07:06,997
(Scoffs)
I Would Never Ask You To Do Anything Wrong,

144
00:07:06,997 --> 00:07:09,098
Ugly Or Morally Suspect.

145
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:11,113
That's What I Have Marc For,
Dear.

146
00:07:11,332 --> 00:07:13,051
W--
Don't Answer Now.

147
00:07:13,356 --> 00:07:16,155
But Don't Throw Your Future Away
At "Player."

148
00:07:21,606 --> 00:07:23,371
She Offered You A Raise, Too?

149
00:07:23,371 --> 00:07:24,623
A Little One, Yeah.

150
00:07:24,656 --> 00:07:27,090
Well, Every Bit Helps
When You Have A New Apartment.

151
00:07:27,122 --> 00:07:30,289
Dad, I Am Not Going To Sell Out
Daniel To Pay My Rent.

152
00:07:30,322 --> 00:07:33,873
You're Not Selling Anyone Out
When You're Making
A Good Career Move.

153
00:07:33,873 --> 00:07:36,122
Aunt Betty, You Have
To Go Back To "Mode."

154
00:07:36,155 --> 00:07:37,828
"Player" Gets Me Nothing.

155
00:07:38,054 --> 00:07:39,780
It's Like I'm Stuck
In A Sand Trap

156
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:41,531
At The Bottom
Of The Ninth Quarter.

157
00:07:43,623 --> 00:07:45,656
Listen To Me.
I'm Already Changing.

158
00:07:45,689 --> 00:07:47,985
Oh, That Reminds Me.
Tony Wanted To Know

159
00:07:47,985 --> 00:07:50,338
If He Could Have One Of Those
Signed "Player" Covers

160
00:07:50,338 --> 00:07:52,689
With All The Star Athletes
For The School Auction.

161
00:07:52,723 --> 00:07:54,976
Oh, Sure. Yeah, Hilda.
I'll Just Ask Daniel

162
00:07:54,976 --> 00:07:58,721
Right After I Tell Him
That His Mortal Enemy
Offered Me A Better Job
With More Pay.

163
00:07:58,756 --> 00:08:00,474
Opportunities
Are Coming Your Way.

164
00:08:00,474 --> 00:08:03,990
This Is Something
To Be Proud Of.
I Don't Think That's How
Daniel's Gonna See It, Dad.

165
00:08:04,023 --> 00:08:07,589
I Feel Like I Was Cheating
St <I>Talking</I> To Wilhelmina.
You're Not Cheating.

166
00:08:07,623 --> 00:08:09,556
It's Not Cheating
To Explore Other Options

167
00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:11,568
Because Your Situation
Is At A Dead End.

168
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:16,114
I Just--I Care About You.
That's All.

169
00:08:17,342 --> 00:08:18,779
Well, One Thing Is For Sure.

170
00:08:18,779 --> 00:08:20,453
I Have To Go In There
First Thing In The Morning

171
00:08:20,453 --> 00:08:22,022
And Tell Daniel
That I Spoke To Wilhelmina,

172
00:08:22,022 --> 00:08:24,552
Because Secrets In That Place
Have A Way Of Going Bad.

173
00:08:30,094 --> 00:08:32,314
Someone's Working Late.

174
00:08:32,677 --> 00:08:34,908
Yeah. I Just Came By
To Pick Up A Little Homework.

175
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:36,750
Lucky I Ran Into You.

176
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:39,470
I Want To Make Sure You're
Coming To My Launch Party.

177
00:08:40,184 --> 00:08:43,218
(Scoffs)
Well, I Hadn't Really--
Wonderful. You Know,
I'm So Glad We're Talking.

178
00:08:43,251 --> 00:08:46,137
I Know It Seems Like I'm Trying
To Poach Your Assistant.

179
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:47,774
(Laughs) Excuse Me?

180
00:08:47,774 --> 00:08:49,463
Oh,
Betty Did Tell You We Spoke

181
00:08:49,463 --> 00:08:51,438
About Her Coming To Work For Me,
Didn't She?

182
00:08:51,438 --> 00:08:54,077
I Mean, I Know You Two
Have No Secrets.

183
00:08:58,624 --> 00:09:00,692
Mm. Good. It's All
Out In The Open Then.

184
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:02,218
Of Course
It's Out In The Open.

185
00:09:02,699 --> 00:09:05,438
I Mean, Everything's
Out In The Open
Between Me And Betty.
(Ding)

186
00:09:06,448 --> 00:09:09,237
How Could You Hide This
From Me?
I'm Sorry. I'm Sorry.

187
00:09:09,237 --> 00:09:12,271
God, Just The Thought Of It,
You Sitting At Her Desk,

188
00:09:12,304 --> 00:09:14,371
Rolling Calls For Her?!

189
00:09:14,404 --> 00:09:16,738
Daniel,
I Don't Want To Leave You.

190
00:09:16,771 --> 00:09:19,069
Then Why Are You
Going Behind My Back?
It Wasn't Like That.

191
00:09:19,069 --> 00:09:20,995
Okay, Well, Tell Me
What Happened, Please.

192
00:09:21,155 --> 00:09:25,276
You Met With Her, She Offered
You A Job And You Didn't Say No.

193
00:09:25,276 --> 00:09:26,841
Daniel,
Working At "Player" Magazine

194
00:09:26,841 --> 00:09:28,952
Isn't Exactly My Dream Job.

195
00:09:32,681 --> 00:09:34,092
I'm Not Happy Here.

196
00:09:34,955 --> 00:09:36,576
I Am.

197
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:38,276
Are You?

198
00:09:38,309 --> 00:09:40,709
Just Stop Right Now.

199
00:09:40,743 --> 00:09:43,908
I'm Not Leaving.
Do You Understand?

200
00:09:43,942 --> 00:09:46,046
This Is What I Want.

201
00:09:46,242 --> 00:09:48,908
Well, Maybe It's
Not What <I>I</I> Want.

202
00:09:48,942 --> 00:09:52,235
Look, You Want To Go Workfor Wilhelmina ???

203
00:09:52,878 --> 00:09:56,247
