I Thought I Could Work For You,
But I Can't.

698
00:36:27,263 --> 00:36:29,730
I Do Want To Be Successful,

699
00:36:29,764 --> 00:36:31,163
Just...

700
00:36:31,197 --> 00:36:33,230
Not By Hurting People.

701
00:36:34,697 --> 00:36:36,765
I Really Misjudged You,
Betty.

702
00:36:36,963 --> 00:36:40,030
Under Those Gaping Pores
And Caveman Eyebrows,

703
00:36:40,063 --> 00:36:42,730
I Thought You Were Smart.

704
00:36:42,764 --> 00:36:45,464
You Think Life Is All About
Who's Right And Who's Wrong,

705
00:36:45,497 --> 00:36:48,330
But History Is Written
By Those Who Win,

706
00:36:48,363 --> 00:36:50,931
Not By Those
Who Are The Nicest.

707
00:36:52,397 --> 00:36:54,797
Enjoy Your Party.

708
00:36:56,330 --> 00:36:59,764
Betty, Why Don't You Stay?

709
00:36:59,797 --> 00:37:03,430
This Party Is About
To Get Very Interesting.

710
00:37:22,996 --> 00:37:23,660
(Tony) Hello?

711
00:37:23,660 --> 00:37:27,230
Hey, Tony. Are--Are You Here
Yet? 'Cause I Don't See You.

712
00:37:27,263 --> 00:37:29,658
Oh, Hey... Bobby. Uh, Sorry
I Didn't Call You Back.

713
00:37:29,658 --> 00:37:32,155
I Had A Family Thing
Come Up.

714
00:37:33,263 --> 00:37:35,897
She Didn't Go Out Of Town?
You're Not Coming?

715
00:37:35,931 --> 00:37:37,397
Yeah, That's Right.

716
00:37:37,430 --> 00:37:39,386
Um, Can I Follow Up
With You Tomorrow?

717
00:37:39,963 --> 00:37:41,462
Is She There With You Now?

718
00:37:41,462 --> 00:37:43,902
Sure. Sounds Good. All Right,
We'll--We'll Talk Tomorrow.

719
00:37:52,363 --> 00:37:53,864
Honestly, Alexis,

720
00:37:53,897 --> 00:37:56,497
If This Is About A Bunch
Of Ridiculous Letters,

721
00:37:56,530 --> 00:37:58,619
I Can Assure You--
This Isn't
Just About The Letters.

722
00:37:58,619 --> 00:38:01,363
I'm Not Happy
With The Magazine.

723
00:38:01,397 --> 00:38:04,096
I Think Your Cover Is Cold.

724
00:38:04,130 --> 00:38:07,096
Well, I Had
A Very Specific Vision.

725
00:38:07,130 --> 00:38:09,063
I Didn't Expect You
To Understand It.

726
00:38:09,096 --> 00:38:11,764
Well, I Guess It Was Lost
On A Few Other People, Too.

727
00:38:11,797 --> 00:38:15,297
Your First Day
Sales Numbers Are In...

728
00:38:15,330 --> 00:38:18,230
And They're Not Good.
Impossible.

729
00:38:18,263 --> 00:38:22,096
Your Relaunch Of "Mode" Is Our
Lowest Selling Issue In Months.

730
00:38:22,130 --> 00:38:24,831
While You're Valued Here
As Our Creative Director,

731
00:38:24,864 --> 00:38:26,538
I've Made A Decision.

732
00:38:26,538 --> 00:38:28,263
If You'll Excuse Me.

733
00:38:28,297 --> 00:38:31,597
Ladies And Gentlemen,
If I Could Have Your Attention.

734
00:38:31,860 --> 00:38:35,128
I'm Happy To Announce That
Tonight We Are Welcoming Back

735
00:38:35,128 --> 00:38:39,127
As Editor-In-Chief Of
"Mode" Magazine--Daniel Meade.

736
00:38:51,938 --> 00:38:53,116
Betty.

737
00:38:54,196 --> 00:38:55,462
Marc.

738
00:38:56,219 --> 00:38:57,832
Well, Here We Are,

739
00:38:57,953 --> 00:39:00,719
As If Nothing's Changed.

740
00:39:00,753 --> 00:39:03,286
You Left Those Letters For Me,
Didn't You?

741
00:39:03,319 --> 00:39:06,292
You Planned This Whole Thing
So That I Would
Be Back With Daniel

742
00:39:06,292 --> 00:39:08,544
And You Could Have Wilhelmina
All To Yourself.

743
00:39:08,544 --> 00:39:11,362
Oh. Don't Be Absurd.

744
00:39:11,362 --> 00:39:14,244
I Would Never Do Anything
To Hurt
Wilhelmina's Interests...

745
00:39:16,553 --> 00:39:18,388
Unless They're Hurting Mine.

746
00:39:23,085 --> 00:39:25,953
Don't Forget. I Still Own
A Third Of This Company.

747
00:39:25,986 --> 00:39:29,452
Your <I>Unborn Child</I> Owns A Third
Of This Company, Not You.

748
00:39:29,486 --> 00:39:32,278
 <I>You</I> Would Be Nothing
Without That Baby.

749
00:39:32,278 --> 00:39:34,458
But Don't Worry. You're Still
Our Creative Director.

750
00:39:34,553 --> 00:39:37,411
Yeah, And I'm More Than Happy
To Have You Come Work For Me.

751
00:39:37,747 --> 00:39:39,413
You Can't Push Me Aside.

752
00:39:40,449 --> 00:39:41,891
Oh, Really?

753
00:39:54,803 --> 00:39:57,437
You Are Gonna Regret This.
I Swear.

754
00:39:57,470 --> 00:40:01,631
Don't You Ever Threaten
My Children, Wilhelmina.

755
00:40:02,669 --> 00:40:07,870
You Have No Idea The Lengths
I Will Go To Protect Them.

756
00:40:23,515 --> 00:40:25,683
Look, Daniel, I'm Sorry.
Look, Betty,
I Never Wanted You To Leave.

757
00:40:25,683 --> 00:40:28,809
I Would Never Even Consider
Working For That--
Me First. Please.

758
00:40:28,809 --> 00:40:31,212
Um, Thank You...

759
00:40:32,502 --> 00:40:34,418
For Having Faith In Me.

760
00:40:34,502 --> 00:40:36,787
That's What Friends Are For.

761
00:40:39,999 --> 00:40:41,754
You're Coming Back, Right?

762
00:40:42,435 --> 00:40:44,369
Well, That Depends...

763
00:40:44,369 --> 00:40:48,106
On Whether Or Not I Can Keep
The Raise Wilhelmina Gave Me.

764
00:40:49,410 --> 00:40:51,864
??

765
00:40:52,614 --> 00:40:54,178
It's Good To Have You Back,
Daniel.

766
00:40:55,196 --> 00:40:56,628
It's Good To Be Back.

767
00:40:58,281 --> 00:40:59,998
Now Seriously,
About The Raise--

768
00:40:59,998 --> 00:41:03,914
You Know, Once You Go There,
You Can't Really Go Back.
(Laughs) Really?

769
